<seg id=1> Chinese Investment Enterprises Become Largest Foreign Investors in Macao </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Macao, April 3, Telegram (Reporter Wang Zhigen, Che Yuming):  Macao China Enterprise Association President Zhang Xuming said that there are currently more than 200 Chinese investment enterprises in Macao with a total capital exceeding 90 billion Macao patacas. </seg>
<seg id=3> Chinese investors have already become the largest foreign investors in Macao. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Zhang Xuming said at a joint meeting commemorating the fifth anniversary of the establishment of the China-China Enterprise Association that Macao's inland investment enterprises range from small to large, weak to strong, and have developed into a strong force in the Macao economy. </seg>
<seg id=5> These enterprises have made a stable and important contribution to the prosperity of Macao. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Based on information received, these enterprises have broadly participated in management activities in many areas, including Macao's trade, industry, finance, insurance, travel, food and drink, transportation and shipping, and construction real estate. </seg>
<seg id=7> Of these, Chinese investment currently accounts for 50 percent of financial insurance, 50-70 percent of the travel industry, 30 percent of imports and exports, and 70 percent of real estate. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Zhang Xuming indicated that Macao's Chinese investment enterprises will continue to be guided by Deng Xiaoping's "One country, two systems" concept and China's various guidelines and policies for Hong Kong and Macao and will adhere to the principle of "There are things that must be done and things that must not be done".  They will strive together with local people in industry and commerce to promote economic stability and social development in Macao and contribute even more. </seg>
</p>
